Homeadmin2016-12-08T15:04:04+00:00 

Vernon Nagel, Inc.
Vernon Nagel, Inc. is a leader in general infrastructure construction. We’ve been digging, building, and constructing throughout the Midwest since 1950. Our work includes roadway construction, underground utilities, bridges, structures, earthwork and sitework. We specialize in earthwork such as pond excavation, multi-acre mass excavations, landfill cell construction, site development and more. Based in Napoleon, Oh we have extensive resources that include talented people, state-of-the-art equipment and unparalleled experience.
Join Our Team
Learn More
ROADWAY/ GENERAL
CONSTRUCTION
From multi-lane highways to city streets to residential driveways, roads are an essential component of our transportation system.
Learn More
UNDERGROUND
UTILITIES
From supplying water to a major city or to sewers and drainage, our underground infrastructure plays a crucial role in our way of life.
Learn More
BRIDGE/
STRUCTURES
Bridges, culverts, and structures are essential parts of our diverse transportation network.  These structures need constant upkeep, repair and replacement.
Learn More
EARTHWORK
SITEWORK
From residential ponds to multi-acre mass excavations, from landfill cell construction, site development, and building pad construction to lakes and lagoons, Vernon Nagel, Inc. can meet the demand.
